50|$|Gunnar Beck read politics, philosophy, law and {{economics}} in Germany and Great Britain and completed his doctorate in political and legal philosophy {{under the supervision of}} Professor Sir Isaiah Berlin in 1996 at Nuffield College, Oxford. He subsequently worked for the international law firm Herbert Smith and as Deputy Legal <b>Adviser</b> (<b>EU</b> law) at the House of Commons of the United Kingdom Parliament. He currently combines academic work with legal practice as a specialist EU lawyer.|$|R

